# Agent Workbench ‚Äî Cursor rules

This project uses the agent-workbench standard dev-workflow. Skills live in
`.cursor/rules/` (installed from `skills/` + `adapters/claude/rules/` in the
agent-workbench repo).

## Pipeline

`incept` ‚Üí `tech-incept` ‚Üí `tech-discovery` (optional) ‚Üí `write-plan` ‚Üí
`plan-review` (optional) ‚Üí `execute-plan` ‚Üí `git-pr` / `github-pr-description`

Each skill produces a single artifact under
`$ARTIFACT_DIR/<scope>/<slug>/<slug>-*.md`. See `.cursor/rules/30-artifact-dir.md`
for `<scope>` resolution.

## Hard rules

- Resolve `$ARTIFACT_DIR` from environment ‚Äî never hardcode vault paths.
- Use slug-prefixed filenames under `$ARTIFACT_DIR/<scope>/<slug>/`.
- Confirm the final path before writing the first artifact in a new scope.
- Skills are deterministic and bounded ‚Äî prefer bounded changes over broad
  rewrites.

## Coding standards

See `.cursor/rules/10-coding-standards.md` for project coding conventions
(installed alongside this file).
